words:
This is you.

Try moving around the screen.
When you hit an edge on the screen, 
you will appear on the other side of the screen. 
Try it! 

Press spacebar to continue.

The square will not move as smoothly as you move the mouse,
but it’s pretty close! This is the amount of turbulence you’ll experience in this experiment. 

Press spacebar to continue.

In each trial, there will be two hidden environments on the screen.
This screen is now filled with the sand environment. 
Try moving in the sand. 

As the sand shifts beneath you, your square will jitter randomly.

Press spacebar to continue.

The other environment is water. 
The screen is now filled with water. 
Try moving in the water. 

Notice how the waves in the water will push you from side to side.

Press spacebar to continue.

In this screen, like in the actual experiment,
half the screen is sand and the other half water.
Which side is which is random on each trial.

You can quickly jump to one half of the screen
by pressing ‘Q’ and ‘R’. Try it!

Press spacebar to continue.

In the task, there will be four squares on screen.
Your task will be to figure out which of the four squares you control. 
Your square will not always be the same colour.
Here square ‘1’ is you.

Press spacebar to continue.

You can select a square to focus on by pressing and holding the square's number on your keyboard.

If you don’t select a square using your keyboard, none of the squares will move. 

The selected square will move more slowly than the others so that it’s easier to see. 
The colour of the selected square is displayed around the edges of the screen. 
You can change your selection as often as you like.

Press spacebar to continue.

On each trial, you will have 15 seconds to figure out which square you control.
Then you’ll have to answer some questions about your experience of the trial.

Press spacebar to continue.

And sometimes, like on this screen, you won’t control any of the squares. 

Press spacebar to continue.

After each trial, you’ll be asked three questions:
1) Which square did you control, if any? 
2) How confident are you that you controlled that square? 
3) How much agency/control did you feel?

In the next block, you’ll get to try six practice trials. 
In these trials, you’ll get feedback about your response. 
In the real task, you won’t get told whether you were correct or not. 

Press spacebar to continue.
